      <body>
         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Melbourne, ¶ 25 June 1888 ¶ T.R. Wilson Esqr ¶ Undersecretary. ¶ Sir...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">88.06.25a</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Thomas Wilson<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
            </p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">L88/6184, unit 350, VPRS 3992/P inward registered correspondence, VA 475 Chief Secretary's Department, Public Record Office, Victoria.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Melbourne,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">25 June 1888</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">T.R. Wilson Esqr</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Undersecretary.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Sir</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>As the work on the Australian Acacias, as regards the main volume<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>B88.13.01.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>is now completed, I have the honor to suggest, that a nicely<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>bound copy may be presented to his Excellency the Governor, also to the Honorable the Chief Secretary, and that one may also — elegantly bound — be furnished for the Centennial Exhibition.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Centennial International Exhibition, Melbourne, 1888-9. The Chief Secretary, A. Deakin, approved M's suggestions on 9 July 1888, 'except for C.S. for whom a plain copy will do'. M was informed of this decision the same day and replied<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>the next day<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>'with best thanks'. The Government Printer was notified of the Minister's authority on 12 July and acknowledged the decision<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>on 30<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>July.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">I have the honor to be,</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Sir, your obedient servant</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
         </div>
      </body>
   </text>
